The paper deals with the theoretical analysis of the MapReduce framework, which is a distributed computing paradigm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with graph connectivity, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses lower bounds, which is a topic in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
